Colour. Body dorsally (
Fig. 1
) mainly blackish brown with yellow markings. Head with median longitudinal stripe and anterior part yellow except along midline. Pronotum with two broad yellow sublateral stripes and thin median stripe. Mesonotum with two sublateral stripes, median stripe not distinct. Dorsum of abdomen totally brown. Antennal and leg segments mainly dark yellow. Fore femur (
Fig. 4
) with one broad dark brown stripe on exterior side and one slender, shorter brown stripe on extensor side. Venter yellow, mesosternum with paired black patches behind fore coxae and with the most posterior region black.

Structural characteristics. Head width 0.98 , interocular width 0.51 , eye size (length, dorsal view) 0.52 . Lengths of antennal segments (
Fig. 1
): 1.21 : 1.13 : 1.11 : 1.56 , first segment with three long spines on distal part. Head length 0.90 , pronotum length 0.59 , mesonotum length 1.24 . Lengths of meso- and metasterna (in ventral view of specimen!), 1.75 : 0.12 . Mesosternum (
Fig. 2
) strongly modified, with medial, posteriorly widened depression in posterior half and with strong transverse swelling at hind margin; depression with black setae directed to its centre; swelling with densely set, long, stout, black, posterodorsad directed setae covering base of metasternum. Metasternum ca. 0.21 long (median length in perpendicular view!), oriented almost vertically, forming a step between mesosternum and base of abdomen (
Fig. 2
). Lengths of leg segments (femur: tibia: tarsal segment 1 : tarsal segment 2 ): fore leg: 1.43 : 1.19 : 0.13 : 0.27 ; middle leg: 4.61 : 3.27 : 0.19 : 0.43 ; hind leg: 4.39 : 3.14 : 0.19 : 0.38 . Fore femur (
Fig. 4
) incrassate basally and tapering towards apex, width of fore femur 0.31 ; fore tibia (
Fig. 4
) strongly curved, basal part with patch of long hairs on flexor side. Middle and hind femora slender and longer than body length (
Fig. 1
); spines on middle femur scattered and not distinct. Middle and hind claws similar to each other, subequal to first tarsal segment, length of each: 0.17 . Abdomen (
Fig. 2
) very short, length of sterna 2–7 combined: 0.57 ; ventrally caudal opening of segment 7 fully exposed (after dissection of segment 8 and genitalia) and occupying three-fourths of that length. Abdominal sterna 2–6 visible as very narrow transverse strips, each of about 0.03 in length, all without median groove. Ventral length of abdominal segment 8 : 0.30 . Pygophore small, sub-oval; proctiger (
Fig. 5
) short, apex with obtuse angle; paramere ( Figs. 7, 8 ) short, simple; endosoma structures as in
Figure 10
.
